# Video Upload 2.1 — Upload video

## Goal

Allow a logged-in user to upload a video file with an optional caption.

---

## Start State

- User authentication is implemented
- Logged-in user exists in session
- No upload functionality exists

---

## End State

- User can upload a video file
- Video is saved locally in `public/uploads/`
- A database record is created for the video
- User is redirected after successful upload

---

## Scope

Included:

- Create upload page `/upload`
- Create upload form (file + caption)
- Validate file type (MP4 only)
- Validate file size (≤ 100MB)
- Save file to `public/uploads/`
- Create DB record in `Video` table

---

## Out of Scope

- Video duration validation
- Progress indicators
- Video compression
- Error retry logic
- File storage outside local disk
- UI polish

---

## Acceptance Criteria

- Upload form is visible at `/upload`
- User can select a video file
- Only MP4 files are accepted
- File is saved in `public/uploads/`
- A video record is created in DB
- User is redirected after upload

---

## Manual Test Steps

1. Start the app
2. Log in
3. Navigate to `/upload`
4. Select an MP4 file
5. Add optional caption
6. Submit form
7. Confirm:
   - File appears in `public/uploads/`
   - DB record exists
   - User is redirected

